e 0 has a\nhigher priority than device 1, and device 2 has the lowest priority.\nHence, for example, device 2 will only receive a grant if it is the only\ndevice making a request when the FSM is in state _A_. Once a device, _i_,\nis given a grant by the FSM, that device continues to receive the grant\nas long as its request, _r[i]_ = 1.\n\nImplement a module that represents this FSM. Use separate always blocks\nfor the state table and the state flip-flops, as done in lectures.\nDescribe the FSM outputs, _g[i]_, using either continuous assignment\nstatement(s) or an always block (at your discretion). Assign any state\ncodes that you wish to use. Assume all sequential logic is triggered on\nthe positive edge of the clock.\n\n\n</input_spec>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nAnother agent has generated a testbench regarding the given input_spec:\n<testbench>\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: Unlicense\n`timescale 1ps/1ps\nmodule tb();\n  logic clk = 0;\n  logic resetn;\n  logic [2:0] r;\n  logic [2:0] g;\n  logic [2:0] g_ref;\n  reg [2:0] input_queue [0:9];\n  reg [2:0] got_output_queue [0:9];\n  reg [2:0] golden_queue [0:9];\n  reg reset_queue [0:9];\n  localparam MAX_QUEUE_SIZE = 8;\n\n  // State parameters\n  localparam [2:0] A = 0, B = 1, C = 2, D = 3;\n  reg [2:0] current_state, next_state;\n\n  // Instantiate DUT\n  TopModule dut(clk, resetn, r, g);\n\n  // Instantiate reference module\n  RefModule ref_mod(clk, resetn, r, g_ref);\n\n  initial begin\n    clk = 0;\n    forever #5 clk = ~clk;\n  end\n\n  // Sequence detection for mismatches\n  always @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\n    if (input_queue.size() >= MAX_QUEUE_SIZE - 1) begin\n      input_queue.delete(0);\n      got_output_queue.delete(0);\n      golden_queue.delete(0);\n      reset_queue.delete(0);\n    end\n\n    input_queue.push_back(r);\n    got_output_queue.push_back(g);\n    golden_queue.push_back(g_ref);\n    reset_queue.push_back(resetn);\n\n    if (g !== g_ref) begin\n      $display("SIMULATION FAILED - 1 MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME %t", $time);\n      $display("Cycle 0, reset %b, input %b, got output %b, exp output %b", 0, reset_queue[0], input_queue[0], got_output_queue[0], golden_queue[0]);\n      $finish;\n    end\n  end\n\n  // Stimulus generation\n  initial begin\n    resetn = 0;\n    r = 0;\n    current_state = A;\n    next_state = A;\n\n    // Reset sequence\n    resetn = 0;\n    #10 resetn = 1;\n\n    // Test scenario 1: Device 0 gets grant\n    r = 3\'b001;\n    @(posedge clk);\n    // Additional stimulus... (omitted for brevity)\n\n    // Test scenario 2: Device 1 gets grant after others are done\n    // (Placeholder for actual test steps)\n\n    // Test scenario 3: Device 2 gets grant after others are done\n    // (Placeholder for actual test steps)\n\n    // Final check and finish\n    #100;\n    if ($error_count == 0) begin\n      $display("SIMULATION PASSED");\n    end\n    $finish;\n  end\nendmodule\n\n</testbench>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nThe module interface is given below:\n<module_interface>\nmodule TopModule (input clk, input resetn, input [2:0] r, output logic [2:0] g);\n</module_interface>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nYour response will be processed by a program, not human.\nSo, please STRICTLY FOLLOW the output format given as XML tag content below to generate a VALID JSON OBJECT:\n<output_format>\n{\n    "reasoning": "All reasoning steps and advices to avoid syntax error",\n    "module": "Pure SystemVerilog code, a complete module"\n}\n</output_format>\nDO NOT include any other information in your response, like \'json\', \'reasoning\' or \'<output_format>\'.\n\nOther requirements:\n1. Don\'t use state_t to define the parameter. Use `localparam` or Use \'reg\' or 